import {square, blank} from "rune";
import {show, animate_rune, color} from "rune";
import {stack, beside} from "rune";

// --- Quad Tree Parser ----------------------------

"Used to give white and dark squares";
"slightly random colours to showcase";
"the quad tree implementation";
const patchwork = true;

const black = ()=>{
    const x = math_random() * 0.05;
    return patchwork
        ? color(square, x, x, x)
        : square;
};
const white = ()=>{
    const x = math_random() * 0.05 + 0.95;
    return patchwork
        ? color(square, x, x, x)
        : blank;
};
const combine = (r1,r2,r3,r4) => {
    return stack(beside(r1,r2),beside(r4,r3));
};

"Data will be in the format:";
"0 -> black color, no children";
"1 -> white color, no children";
"2 -> 4 children";

"Data will be parsed as such:";
"0 -> generate square";
"1 -> generate blank";
"2 -> performs parseIter on the 4 children values";
"210201110 as an example";
"abbbccccb -> a being 1st layer, b is 2nd, c is 3rd";
"parseIter will return the ending index, ";
"so previous call can continue where it left off";

"Children are ordered in clockwise fashion";
"Starting from the top left corner";

const parseData = (dataStr)=>{
    const parseIter = (start)=>{
        if (char_at(dataStr, start)==="0") {
            return [black(),start+1];
        } else if (char_at(dataStr, start)==="1") {
            return [white(),start+1];
        } else {
            let output = parseIter(start+1);
            let r1 = output[0];
            output = parseIter(output[1]);
            let r2 = output[0];
            output = parseIter(output[1]);
            let r3 = output[0];
            output = parseIter(output[1]);
            let r4 = output[0];
            return [combine(r1,r2,r3,r4), output[1]];
        }
    };
    return parseIter(0)[0];
};

// --- Animation functions --------------

const generateFrameFunctionCreator = (frame_data,frames,fps)=>{
    const generateFrame = (timestamp) => {
        const index = math_round(timestamp * fps)%frames;
        const rune = parseData(frame_data[index]);
        return rune;
    };
    
    return generateFrame;
};

const frames = 800;
const fps = 20;
const duration = frames/fps;

animate_rune(
        duration, 
        fps, 
        generateFrameFunctionCreator(
                frame_data, 
                frames, 
                fps));
